# Loaded only by `npm run build:apk` (vite --mode capacitor), on top of the
# values in .env. The Capacitor WebView has no dev proxy and isn't same-origin
# with the backend, so the API needs an absolute URL here.
#
# - Testing on a physical device over your own WiFi: use this machine's LAN
#   IP (ipconfig / `Get-NetIPAddress`), e.g. http://192.168.0.4:8000/api.
#   The phone and this machine must be on the same network, and the backend
#   must be running with --host 0.0.0.0 (already the default in run.py).
# - Testing in an Android emulator: the emulator's alias for the host
#   machine is 10.0.2.2, e.g. http://10.0.2.2:8000/api.
# - Real release build: point this at your deployed backend's HTTPS URL.
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.0.4:8000/api
